          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were a special project of your sire's. Long had he tried to infiltrate the Sabbat, only to be rebuffed by the solid wall of Faith which protects the sect from just such infiltration. Your sire was educated in London, where the Egyptian origins of the Setites are at odds with the Biblical origins of the Sabbat. Until one night, when reading the sacred texts, he had an insight. And you were the result of that insight. A newly Embraced Setite, part of your education consisted of the belief that Caine, the father of vampires and the deity of reverence among the Sabbat; and Set, the founder of your clan, are one and the same. Practically every other vampire, Setite and Sabbat alike, defies this belief. But your sire used some very... vigorous techniques to ensure you were inculcated with the proper amount of belief. Thus believing, you are capable of functioning in the Sabbat - and as a priest no less! However, you must always step carefully. Though the belief is enough for you, you would almost assuredly be executed for heresy should anyone else find out how you've twisted Sabbat doctrine. Especially because you are still a faithful Setite, maintaining ties to your parent clan and upholding the Independent Alliance to the best of your abilities. Tonight, you are traveling with a Giovanni 'packmate' in an attempt to disrupt the Sabbat's plans for a coordinated strike against the holdings in Orange County."
        ],
